The article announces that various government officials, including the President, First Lady, Vice President, and Cabinet Secretaries, will participate in memorial events and community service projects in honor of Martin Luther King, Jr. Day. The Martin Luther King, Jr. Day of Service is an opportunity for Americans to come together and help meet the needs of their communities. The day will include thousands of projects across the country. The article provides a list of Cabinet Secretaries and Administration officials who will be participating in events in Washington, D.C., Atlanta, Georgia, and elsewhere. The events range from service projects to speeches and ceremonies honoring Dr. King's legacy.